    "result": {"data":{"markdownRemark":{"excerpt":"Hi Friends üëã, Welcome To aGuideHub!  To make mui icon button with badge in react js, you have to use  component in icon Button component. It will make mui icon‚Ä¶","html":"<p>Hi Friends üëã,</p>\n<p>Welcome To aGuideHub! </p>\n<p>To make mui icon button with badge in react js, you have to use <code class=\"language-text\">Badge</code> component in icon Button component. It will make mui icon button with badge in React JS.</p>\n<p>Today, I am going to show you, How to make mui icon button with badge in react js</p>\n<h2>Installation</h2>\n<p>Install the following packages to use mui icon button in react js.</p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">npm</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">npm install @mui<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>material @emotion<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>react @emotion<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>styled</code></pre></div>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">yarn</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">yarn add @mui<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>material @emotion<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>react @emotion<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>styled</code></pre></div>\n<p>Table of contents</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Install MUI and create a new React app.</li>\n<li>Import Material-UI icon button.</li>\n<li>Use the icon button Component.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Step 1: Install MUI and create a new React app.</h3>\n<p>First you have to install the React project. You should use <code class=\"language-text\">create-react-app</code> command to create a new React project.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">npx create<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>react<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app my<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app\ncd my<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app\nnpm start</code></pre></div>\n<h3>Step 2: Import Material-UI icon button.</h3>\n<p>After installing <code class=\"language-text\">MUI</code>, you have to import your React component. To do this, add the following line to the top of your component file.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"react\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> IconButton <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"@mui/material/IconButton\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> Badge <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"@mui/material/Badge\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> ArrowDropDownCircleIcon <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"@mui/icons-material/ArrowDropDownCircle\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<h3>Step 3: Use the icon button Component.</h3>\n<p>Icons are also appropriate for toggle buttons that allow a single choice to be selected or deselected, such as adding or removing a star to an item.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>IconButton color<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"primary\"</span> aria<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>label<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Arrow \"</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>Badge badgeContent<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token number\">4</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> color<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"error\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n        <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>ArrowDropDownCircleIcon <span class=\"token operator\">/</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>Badge<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>IconButton<span class=\"token operator\">></span> </code></pre></div>\n<h2>MUI material make mui icon button with badge example.</h2>\n<p>The below code is an example, you need to import <code class=\"language-text\">icon button</code> Component. Then, you have to use <code class=\"language-text\">Badge</code> component in icon Button component. Then it will make mui icon button with badge in react js.</p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">App.js</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"react\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> IconButton <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"@mui/material/IconButton\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> Badge <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"@mui/material/Badge\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> ArrowDropDownCircleIcon <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"@mui/icons-material/ArrowDropDownCircle\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> <span class=\"token function-variable function\">App</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>IconButton color<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"primary\"</span> aria<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>label<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Arrow \"</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n      <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>Badge badgeContent<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token number\">4</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> color<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"error\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n        <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>ArrowDropDownCircleIcon <span class=\"token operator\">/</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n      <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>Badge<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>IconButton<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">default</span> App<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>In the above code example, I have used the <code class=\"language-text\">@mui/material</code> component and make mui icon button with badge in react js.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 300px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/8ec0e80371ea6777dcc7f0f349165596/c85cb/button-with-badge.webp\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 89.24050632911393%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/webp;base64,UklGRlIAAABXRUJQVlA4IEYAAACQAwCdASoUABIAPtFYpEuoJSOhsAgBABoJZQAAW/CXVTH8b+VAAP4ntiXbOcrdMEIi5GBQA9f0QfodO3+uLIQb8u3wAAAA'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"React, button, with, badge\"\n        title=\"React, button, with, badge\"\n        src=\"/static/8ec0e80371ea6777dcc7f0f349165596/c85cb/button-with-badge.webp\"\n        srcset=\"/static/8ec0e80371ea6777dcc7f0f349165596/81b7c/button-with-badge.webp 158w,\n/static/8ec0e80371ea6777dcc7f0f349165596/c85cb/button-with-badge.webp 300w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Here, we are provided code sandbox links for the above program make mui icon button with badge in react js. Then you can use whenever you want and do the changes as per your requirements.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://aguidehub.com/codesandbox/?code=inspiring-waterfall-7cv2kv\" rel=\"nofollow\"  target=\"_BLANK\" >Try it Yourself</a></p>\n<p>All the best üëç</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"How to make mui icon button with badge in react js?","tags":["React"],"date":"January 11, 2024","description":"Example of make mui icon button with badge in React js with step by step tutorial - aGuideHub","social_image":"media/template/reactjs.jpg"}},"prev":{"frontmatter":{"title":"How to change mui icon button border in react js?"},"fields":{"slug":"/blog/2024-01-11-how-to-change-mui-icon-button-border-in-react-js/"}},"next":{"frontmatter":{"title":"How to use mui icon button as a link in react js?"},"fields":{"slug":"/blog/2024-01-10-how-to-use-mui-icon-button-as-a-link-in-react-js/"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/blog/2024-01-11-how-to-make-mui-icon-button-with-badge-in-react-js/","prevSlug":"/blog/2024-01-11-how-to-change-mui-icon-button-border-in-react-js/","nextSlug":"/blog/2024-01-10-how-to-use-mui-icon-button-as-a-link-in-react-js/"}},
